# Security Notice
# 
# This directory contains SENSITIVE API KEYS and CREDENTIALS.
# 
# Files that should NEVER be committed to git:
#   - *.txt files (except .gitkeep and README.md)
#   - *.pem, *.key files
#   - Any file containing API keys, secrets, or private data
#
# Only these files should be in git:
#   - .gitkeep (this file)
#   - README.md (documentation)
#   - *.example files (templates without real values)
#
# If you accidentally commit a secret:
#   1. IMMEDIATELY rotate/revoke the exposed credential
#   2. Remove from git history: git filter-branch --force --index-filter 'git rm --cached --ignore-unmatch secrets/FILE' HEAD
#   3. Force push: git push --force
#   4. Notify security team if applicable
